# Environment Variables for Claude Code Multi-Agent System
# Copy this file to .env and replace the placeholder values with your actual credentials

# =============================================================================
# FIRECRAWL MCP CONFIGURATION
# =============================================================================
# Required for the research-agent to scrape documentation and perform research
# Get your API key from: https://firecrawl.dev
# Format: fc-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
firecrawl-api-key=your-firecrawl-api-key-here

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: ADDITIONAL MCP SERVERS
# =============================================================================
# Add other MCP server configurations as needed
# Examples:
# openai-api-key=your-openai-api-key-here
# anthropic-api-key=your-anthropic-api-key-here

# =============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT SETTINGS
# =============================================================================
# Uncomment and modify these settings for development/debugging
# LOG_LEVEL=debug
# MCP_DEBUG=true

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file: cp example.env .env
# 2. Edit .env with your actual API keys
# 3. Run the setup script: ./setup-firecrawl-mcp.sh
# 4. Restart Claude Code
# 5. Test with: "Research React documentation for our project"
#
# SECURITY NOTE: 
# - Never commit .env file to version control
# - .env is already in .gitignore for security
# - Keep your API keys private and secure